
⚙️ Data Transformer Engine (50-Logic Challenge Suite)
A high-performance JavaScript utility designed to master Array Methods, Data Immutability, and Complex Aggregations. This project contains 50 logical solutions to real-world data transformation problems, organized into 5 difficulty tiers.

🚀 Key Features
Total Challenges: 50 unique logic implementations.

Complexity: From basic mapping to advanced data pipelines.

Principles: Strictly follows ES6+ standards and Immutability.

Use Case: Simulates data handling for Dashboards, Analytics, and Search Engines.

📊 The 5-Level Logic Roadmap
🟢 Level 1: Basic Transformation (1–10)
Fundamental operations for data cleaning.

Basic .map() for name/age extraction.

Array filtering for active status.

String formatting and Case conversions.

🟡 Level 2: Intermediate Analysis (11–20)
Mathematical and statistical basics.

Payroll calculations using .reduce().

Salary Leaderboards (Highest vs. Lowest).

Frequency counting (Users per city).

🟠 Level 3: Object & Reduce Mastery (21–30)
Complex structural changes.

Dynamic Grouping: Creating {city: [users]} mappings.

Skill Analysis: Flattening nested skill arrays into frequency maps.

Data Tagging: Adding calculated properties like isRich or skillCount.

🔴 Level 4: Chaining & Refined Logic (31–40)
Multi-step processing pipelines.

Skill-Based Search: Finding specific tech-stack experts.

Chained Logic: Filter ➡️ Sort ➡️ Slice for "Top 2 High Earners".

Nested Search: Case-insensitive city and skill filtering.

🔥 Level 5: The "Interview Killer" (41–50)
Advanced algorithms for Senior-level requirements.

Demographic Segmentation: Categorizing users by Age Ranges (20-25, 26-30, etc.).

Global Stats Engine: Automated summaries for the entire dataset.

The Bonus Pipeline: A single generateReport() function that executes a full lifecycle: Filter ➡️ Transform ➡️ Group ➡️ Final Financial Report.

🛠️ Technical Skills Demonstrated
High-Order Functions: .map(), .filter(), .reduce(), .flatMap(), .some(), .every().

Modern ES6+: Spread Operator (...), Destructuring, Set for uniqueness, and Object.entries.

Functional Programming: Writing pure functions that avoid data mutation.

💻 How to Run
Clone the repository.
